---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | Great Yarmouth Plumbers';
const description = 'Privacy Policy for Great Yarmouth Plumbers. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal data in accordance with UK GDPR.';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Privacy Policy' },
];

const lastUpdated = '16 March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />

  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-900 to-brand-800 py-12 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-brand-200">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          {business.name} ("{business.name}", "we", "us", "our") is a plumbing services business based at {business.address.street}, {business.address.city}, {business.address.county}, {business.address.postcode}. We are the data controller for the personal information collected through this website ({business.website}).
        </p>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a> or call us on <a href={business.phoneHref}>{business.phone}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What Personal Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following types of personal data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact information:</strong> name, phone number, email address, and postal address or postcode.</li>
          <li><strong>Job details:</strong> description of your plumbing issue, preferred appointment times, and any notes you provide.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, pages visited, and referring URLs — collected automatically when you visit our website.</li>
          <li><strong>Communications:</strong> records of any messages, emails, or calls between you and us.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Collect Your Data</h2>
        <p>We collect personal data in the following ways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>When you complete a contact or lead capture form on our website.</li>
          <li>When you call or email us directly.</li>
          <li>Automatically through cookies and similar technologies when you browse our website.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Why We Use Your Data (Legal Bases)</h2>
        <p>We process your personal data on the following lawful bases under UK GDPR:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contract performance:</strong> to respond to your enquiry, provide a quote, and carry out the services you request.</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> to improve our services, maintain records, and follow up on job enquiries.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> to comply with applicable laws and regulations (e.g. tax, health and safety).</li>
          <li><strong>Consent:</strong> for marketing communications, where you have opted in. You can withdraw consent at any time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. How We Share Your Data</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share it with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Sub-contractors and engineers</strong> who carry out work on your property on our behalf.</li>
          <li><strong>IT and software providers</strong> who host or process data as part of our operations (e.g. cloud hosting, email services).</li>
          <li><strong>Legal and regulatory authorities</strong> where required by law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Any third parties we share data with are required to handle it securely and in accordance with UK GDPR.</p>

        <h2>6. How Long We Keep Your Data</h2>
        <p>We retain personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes it was collected:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer enquiry and job records: up to 6 years (for accounting and legal purposes).</li>
          <li>Website analytics data: up to 26 months.</li>
          <li>Marketing communications: until you unsubscribe or withdraw consent.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses cookies to improve your experience and to analyse site traffic. Please see our <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a> for full details.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li><strong>Rectify</strong> inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
          <li><strong>Erase</strong> your data ("right to be forgotten") in certain circumstances.</li>
          <li><strong>Restrict</strong> the processing of your data in certain circumstances.</li>
          <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
          <li><strong>Data portability:</strong> receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time where processing is based on consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a>. We will respond within one month.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If you are unhappy with how we handle your personal data, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK's data protection regulator, the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a> or by calling 0303 123 1113.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The most recent version will always be available on this page. We encourage you to review it periodically.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
